  m_text: "- Ph\u1EDF is one of the most famous Vietnamese noodle soups and is often
    eaten for breakfast or lunch.\n\n- The dish is believed to have originated in
    Northern Vietnam before spreading across the country.\n\n- It consists of rice
    noodles served in broth with beef or chicken and fresh herbs.\n\n- Main ingredients
    include broth bones, rice noodles, green onions, cilantro, and spices such as
    cinnamon and star anise."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
